        jTextArea1.setRows(5);
        jTextArea1.setText(" 1. Introduction\n   1.1 These Terms and Conditions apply to all customers using the Hall Booking Management System (\"the System\") operated by Venue Master.\n   1.2 By registering and making bookings through the System, you agree to abide by these Terms and Conditions.\n\n 2. Registration\n   2.1 To make a booking, customers must first register an account with the System by providing accurate personal and contact information.\n   2.2 Customers are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their login credentials and must notify Venue Master. immediately of any unauthorized access to their account.\n\n 3. Booking Process\n   3.1 Availability: Customers can view available halls as per the schedule set by the Scheduler.\n   3.2 Selection: Customers must select their preferred hall type (Auditorium, Banquet Hall, or Meeting Room) based on availability and booking requirements.\n   3.3 Payment: Full payment is required at the time of booking. The booking will only be confirmed upon successful payment.\n   3.4 Receipt: Once payment is completed, a receipt with booking details will be provided. Customers should retain this receipt for future reference.\n\n 4. Cancellation Policy\n   4.1 Customers can cancel their booking, but it must be done at least 3 days before the booking date to be eligible for a full refund.\n   4.2 Cancellations made within 3 days of the booking date are non-refundable.\n   4.3 To cancel a booking, customers must do so through their account in the System.\n\n 5. Booking Modifications\n   5.1 Changes to the booking (e.g., date, time, hall selection) are subject to availability and must be made at least 3 days prior to the original booking date.\n   5.2 Any modifications must be done through the System, and additional charges may apply depending on the changes.\n\n 6. Issues and Complaints\n   6.1 If a customer encounters any issues with a booked hall, they can raise the issue through the System, where the Manager will address it.\n   6.2 Customers can track the progress of their complaints, including the status (e.g., \"In Progress,\" \"Done,\" or \"Closed\").\n\n 7. Liability and Refunds\n   7.1 Venue Master. is not liable for any loss or damage arising from the use of the booked halls, including events that are canceled due to unforeseen circumstances beyond the company’s control.\n   7.2 Refunds will only be issued as per the cancellation policy. No other compensation will be provided for issues arising from the hall's condition or availability, except in cases where Venue Master. is directly responsible for the issue.\n\n 8. Data Privacy\n   8.1 Customer data, including personal and payment information, is stored in a secure manner in text files as per the system’s data management process.\n   8.2 Venue Master. will take reasonable measures to protect customer data but is not liable for any data breaches resulting from external factors beyond its control.\n\n 9. Termination of Service\n   9.1 Venue Master. reserves the right to suspend or terminate customer access to the System in case of any misuse, breach of these Terms and Conditions, or fraudulent activity.\n   9.2 In cases of termination, any future bookings will be automatically canceled, and refunds will be processed according to the cancellation policy.\n\n 10. Amendments\n   10.1 Venue Master. may update these Terms and Conditions from time to time. Customers will be notified of any changes via the System, and continued use of the System after such updates constitutes acceptance of the new terms.\n\n 11. Contact Information\n   11.1 For booking inquiries, cancellations, or any issues related to the use of the System, customers can contact Venue Master. through the provided customer support channels.\n");
